1
00:00:09,036 --> 00:00:09,832
<i>C'mon!</i>

2
00:00:16,177 --> 00:00:18,805
<i>Running like a fugitive,</i>

3
00:00:19,847 --> 00:00:22,008
<i>Being chased by something</i>

4
00:00:23,684 --> 00:00:26,346
<i>Inside my heart is pounding</i>

5
00:00:27,455 --> 00:00:30,083
<i>My throat dry like it's withering</i>

6
00:00:31,792 --> 00:00:34,886
<i>For no single one,</i>

7
00:00:35,529 --> 00:00:38,657
<i>To none does belong,</i>

8
00:00:40,134 --> 00:00:44,503
<i>This time is ours, right now...</i>

9
00:00:47,141 --> 00:00:48,904
<i>Unraveling the pain,</i>

10
00:00:49,010 --> 00:00:50,739
<i>Unraveling our hearts,</i>

11
00:00:50,811 --> 00:00:53,143
<i>Unraveling shadows</i>

12
00:00:54,682 --> 00:00:56,445
<i>Stifling our breath,</i>

13
00:00:56,517 --> 00:00:58,417
<i>Reaching for beyond,</i>

14
00:00:58,486 --> 00:01:00,920
<i>Tearing through the dark</i>

15
00:01:02,823 --> 00:01:09,387
<i>In fighting and in love</i>

16
00:01:10,498 --> 00:01:12,989
<i>To the distant light above,</i>

17
00:01:13,768 --> 00:01:16,635
<i>Yes, we are on the way</i>

18
00:01:21,475 --> 00:01:22,772
<i>I wanna rock...</i>

19
00:01:25,246 --> 00:01:26,770
<i>Rockin' my heart</i>

20
00:01:32,596 --> 00:01:38,398
<i>The Demon in the Snow</i>

21
00:01:39,103 --> 00:01:42,903
Gatô, why did you come here?

22
00:01:44,041 --> 00:01:47,238
And who are those henchmen?

23
00:01:49,079 --> 00:01:51,479
Our strategy has changed
a little...

24
00:01:52,750 --> 00:01:54,843
I'm sorry about this Zabuza,

25
00:01:54,919 --> 00:01:57,888
but you will die here.

26
00:01:59,390 --> 00:02:00,618
What?!

27
00:02:01,292 --> 00:02:04,318
Since hiring a regular Shinobi
costs a lot of money,

28
00:02:04,395 --> 00:02:07,887
I hired Rouge Ninjas like you.

29
00:02:08,265 --> 00:02:09,789
And, it would have been even
more ideal

30
00:02:09,867 --> 00:02:12,461
to save my money and effort if
Ninja-to-Ninja battles

31
00:02:12,536 --> 00:02:14,504
ended in each killing the other off.

32
00:02:14,939 --> 00:02:17,203
Well, you are certainly not worthy
of being called

33
00:02:17,274 --> 00:02:18,605
the Demon of the
Hidden Mist Village.

34
00:02:18,709 --> 00:02:24,079
If you were to ask me,
you're just a cute little demon!

35
00:02:26,450 --> 00:02:28,179
<i>What are those guys?</i>

36
00:02:28,552 --> 00:02:29,814
<i>So many of them...</i>

37
00:02:30,888 --> 00:02:32,981
Kakashi... I apologize.

38
00:02:33,624 --> 00:02:35,285
Our fight ends here...

39
00:02:36,060 --> 00:02:39,154
As long as my reason to
take down Tazuna is gone,

40
00:02:39,396 --> 00:02:42,194
there is no reason to fight you either.

41
00:02:43,500 --> 00:02:45,661
Yeah... you are right.

42
00:02:51,008 --> 00:02:52,373
That reminds me...

43
00:02:52,710 --> 00:02:55,178
I owe him something.

44
00:02:55,446 --> 00:02:59,883
He squeezed my arm'til it broke...

45
00:03:04,722 --> 00:03:06,986
Huh, he's dead.

46
00:03:07,157 --> 00:03:08,624
You bastard!

47
00:03:08,692 --> 00:03:10,717
What do you think you're doing, hey?!

48
00:03:10,861 --> 00:03:13,489
Stop! Don't act so recklessly...!

49
00:03:13,597 --> 00:03:17,260
You say something, too!
He was your comrade, right?

50
00:03:17,968 --> 00:03:21,665
Shut up, punk.
Haku is already dead.

51
00:03:21,739 --> 00:03:22,501
What...?

52
00:03:22,573 --> 00:03:25,701
Don't you feel anything watching
him doing that!

53
00:03:25,943 --> 00:03:28,776
Weren't you with Haku for a long time!

54
00:03:29,813 --> 00:03:36,184
As Gatô used me...
I was simply using Haku.

55
00:03:37,821 --> 00:03:39,254
I thought I'd told you...

56
00:03:40,090 --> 00:03:42,581
We Shinobi are merely tools.

57
00:03:43,594 --> 00:03:48,327
What I wanted were his skills
and not Haku himself.

58
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:52,062
I have no regrets...

59
00:03:53,604 --> 00:03:57,404
Do you...
Do you really mean that?

60
00:03:58,042 --> 00:03:59,100
Naruto, stop.

61
00:03:59,643 --> 00:04:02,737
There's no need to fight
him anymore... Besides...

62
00:04:03,414 --> 00:04:06,941
Shut up!
My enemy is still... this one!

63
00:04:10,888 --> 00:04:12,287
He...

64
00:04:12,790 --> 00:04:16,487
He really liked you!

65
00:04:17,261 --> 00:04:20,253
<i>Is there someone special in your life?</i>

66
00:04:20,597 --> 00:04:22,963
He liked you that much!

67
00:04:23,300 --> 00:04:28,260
<i>When a person feels he wants</i>
<i>to protect a person special to him,</i>

68
00:04:28,572 --> 00:04:31,336
<i>that person can truly become strong.</i>

69
00:04:31,842 --> 00:04:35,403
Even so,
don't you feel anything at all?!

70
00:04:35,779 --> 00:04:39,772
<i>It's difficult for me to completely</i>
<i>become a Shinobi.</i>

71
00:04:40,384 --> 00:04:43,114
You really... honestly...

72
00:04:43,187 --> 00:04:45,485
don't feel anything at all?

73
00:04:47,257 --> 00:04:49,350
<i>I'd like to make that person's</i>
<i>dream come true...</i>

74
00:04:49,426 --> 00:04:52,657
<i>For that, I could completely</i>
<i>become a Shinobi.</i>

75
00:04:53,797 --> 00:04:56,288
When a person becomes
as strong as you...

76
00:04:56,533 --> 00:04:58,865
Does that person really
behave like you?

77
00:05:00,270 --> 00:05:05,435
He threw his life away
for you!

78
00:05:06,376 --> 00:05:08,810
<i>I'd like to make that</i>
<i>person's dream come true...</i>

79
00:05:09,446 --> 00:05:11,971
<i>That is my dream.</i>

80
00:05:14,218 --> 00:05:16,379
He didn't even fulfill his
own dreams and yet...

81
00:05:17,454 --> 00:05:18,944
<i>I was happy.</i>

82
00:05:20,257 --> 00:05:22,282
To die as a tool...!

83
00:05:24,294 --> 00:05:29,755
That's...
That's... too painful...

84
00:05:35,472 --> 00:05:37,235
Kid...

85
00:05:52,689 --> 00:05:56,887
Don't say anything... anymore.

86
00:06:02,499 --> 00:06:03,523
Haku was...

87
00:06:04,101 --> 00:06:06,194
He wasn't just thinking of me.

88
00:06:06,503 --> 00:06:08,733
He was feeling pain inside
for you

89
00:06:08,806 --> 00:06:10,603
while he battled you guys too...

90
00:06:12,176 --> 00:06:16,135
I know.
He was too kind...

91
00:06:18,248 --> 00:06:22,241
I'm glad we could fight with you
at the end.

92
00:06:24,388 --> 00:06:25,286
Huh?

93
00:06:29,560 --> 00:06:34,020
Yes, little punk,
it's as you say, after all...

94
00:06:35,499 --> 00:06:37,194
Shinobi are human too...

95
00:06:38,402 --> 00:06:42,031
Maybe it's impossible to become
an emotionless tool...

96
00:06:44,441 --> 00:06:47,001
I've lost.

97
00:06:50,747 --> 00:06:52,612
Kid! Give me the Kunai knife!

98
00:06:59,356 --> 00:07:00,220
Okay...

99
00:07:11,134 --> 00:07:11,862
What?!

100
00:07:12,469 --> 00:07:15,404
Enough! Take them down!

101
00:07:15,505 --> 00:07:16,870
Right!

102
00:07:18,075 --> 00:07:19,337
Are you crazy?

103
00:07:19,409 --> 00:07:21,673
Do you think you can win by yourself
against this many of us?

104
00:07:55,512 --> 00:07:56,979
D-Demon!

105
00:08:13,730 --> 00:08:18,394
If you're so anxious
to join your friend...

106
00:08:18,502 --> 00:08:21,869
you go ahead... alone!

107
00:08:22,306 --> 00:08:24,137
Unfortunately...

108
00:08:24,308 --> 00:08:30,611
I don't... intend on going...
to the same place... as Haku!

109
00:08:30,914 --> 00:08:34,509
W-What?! Pretending to be so tough...

110
00:08:35,218 --> 00:08:40,622
You're going to hell with me!

111
00:08:42,092 --> 00:08:43,957
It's no big deal...

112
00:08:44,061 --> 00:08:47,030
When the Demon of
the Hidden Mists Village

113
00:08:47,097 --> 00:08:51,056
dies and goes to hell,
he can become a real demon.

114
00:08:51,501 --> 00:08:53,696
Look forward to it!

115
00:08:54,004 --> 00:08:56,165
I'll let you find out
for sure

116
00:08:56,239 --> 00:08:59,606
if I'm a cute little demon or not in hell!

117
00:09:48,358 --> 00:09:49,689
Haku...

118
00:09:59,770 --> 00:10:04,605
Now... it's goodbye, Haku...

119
00:10:06,443 --> 00:10:09,173
Thanks for everything...

120
00:10:10,213 --> 00:10:11,908
I'm sorry...

121
00:10:23,960 --> 00:10:25,552
Don't look away.

122
00:10:27,097 --> 00:10:30,089
It's the end for
a man who lived fiercely.

123
00:10:31,601 --> 00:10:32,625
Yup...

124
00:10:36,573 --> 00:10:39,064
<i>Did I...die...?</i>

125
00:10:40,610 --> 00:10:41,542
Sasuke!

126
00:10:41,678 --> 00:10:43,236
<i>Sakura...</i>

127
00:10:44,614 --> 00:10:47,583
<i>Am I...am I...?!</i>

128
00:10:50,887 --> 00:10:53,151
Sakura, you're heavy.

129
00:10:53,323 --> 00:10:54,290
Huh?!

130
00:10:55,759 --> 00:10:57,420
Sasuke...

131
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:07,268
Sasuke, Sasuke, Sasuke!

132
00:11:07,404 --> 00:11:09,634
Sakura...
That hurts...

133
00:11:11,308 --> 00:11:13,469
Things turned out well,
didn't they, Sakura?

134
00:11:14,911 --> 00:11:16,811
Stop, you shouldn't move!

135
00:11:17,247 --> 00:11:18,942
Anyway, where's Naruto?

136
00:11:19,716 --> 00:11:22,412
And also,
what happened to that mask guy?

137
00:11:23,019 --> 00:11:24,714
Naruto's fine.

138
00:11:24,921 --> 00:11:29,153
And... the masked kid,
he died...

139
00:11:30,093 --> 00:11:32,789
Died? Did Naruto get him?

140
00:11:33,296 --> 00:11:38,757
Well... I'm not really sure,
but he protected Zabuza...

141
00:11:41,738 --> 00:11:43,638
I had faith in you.

142
00:11:44,074 --> 00:11:45,598
You are awesome, Sasuke!

143
00:11:45,675 --> 00:11:47,802
You avoided getting inflicted with
any mortal wounds!

144
00:11:49,613 --> 00:11:52,241
<i>From the beginning...he intended to...</i>

145
00:11:53,250 --> 00:11:54,547
Naruto!

146
00:11:54,818 --> 00:11:55,876
<i>Sakura...</i>

147
00:11:55,952 --> 00:11:58,853
Sasuke's all right!
He's alive!

148
00:11:59,389 --> 00:12:00,378
Huh?

149
00:12:12,202 --> 00:12:17,196
<i>He was feeling pain inside</i>
<i>for you while he battled you guys too...</i>

150
00:12:17,807 --> 00:12:20,241
<i>He was too kind...</i>

151
00:12:21,711 --> 00:12:23,576
<i>I see... He...</i>

152
00:12:24,247 --> 00:12:26,579
So, Sasuke's all right too...

153
00:12:27,851 --> 00:12:29,045
That's a relief...

154
00:12:30,787 --> 00:12:32,277
Hey, hey, hey!

155
00:12:33,323 --> 00:12:34,881
You guys are too relaxed!

156
00:12:35,559 --> 00:12:39,461
Darn Ninja!
Killing our source of money!

157
00:12:40,030 --> 00:12:41,258
Now that it's come to this,

158
00:12:41,331 --> 00:12:42,821
there's no choice but to attack
the whole town and

159
00:12:42,899 --> 00:12:45,367
take everything valuable!

160
00:12:47,504 --> 00:12:48,630
Shoot, this isn't good!

161
00:12:48,705 --> 00:12:49,865
Kakashi Sensei!

162
00:12:50,140 --> 00:12:52,734
Don't you have a Jutsu
to annihilate them all at once?

163
00:12:52,976 --> 00:12:55,376
That's impossible!
I've used too much Chakra!

164
00:12:56,012 --> 00:12:57,240
Here we go!

165
00:13:07,257 --> 00:13:09,623
Enemies who come any closer
to the island...

166
00:13:10,360 --> 00:13:12,453
With all the might of
all the island's people...

167
00:13:12,529 --> 00:13:14,429
will not be allowed to live!

168
00:13:14,497 --> 00:13:15,759
Yeah!

169
00:13:15,966 --> 00:13:17,024
Inari!

170
00:13:18,535 --> 00:13:21,595
Heroes always arrive
on the scene late!

171
00:13:22,906 --> 00:13:25,807
Inari... You guys...

172
00:13:31,715 --> 00:13:34,548
Okay, I'm gonna help out, too!

173
00:13:34,985 --> 00:13:36,509
Shadow Clone Jutsu!

174
00:13:41,524 --> 00:13:44,254
I can do that even
with my scarce Chakra...

175
00:13:44,327 --> 00:13:45,851
At least, it will bluff...

176
00:13:46,930 --> 00:13:48,192
Shadow Clone Jutsu!

177
00:13:50,300 --> 00:13:51,358
Kakashi Version!

178
00:13:53,970 --> 00:13:56,666
So... are you ready to fight?!

179
00:13:57,007 --> 00:13:58,702
No, we're not!

180
00:14:07,350 --> 00:14:08,544
We've done it!

181
00:14:28,772 --> 00:14:30,637
Sounds like it's over.

182
00:14:31,341 --> 00:14:32,137
Yeah...

183
00:14:34,210 --> 00:14:36,644
Kakashi...
I need to ask you a favor.

184
00:14:37,714 --> 00:14:38,681
What is it?

185
00:14:40,383 --> 00:14:45,719
His...
I want to see his face...

186
00:14:50,160 --> 00:14:51,092
All right.

187
00:15:15,985 --> 00:15:16,917
Huh?

188
00:15:18,355 --> 00:15:19,219
Snow...

189
00:15:19,856 --> 00:15:21,756
Snow at this time
of the year?

190
00:15:31,201 --> 00:15:34,864
<i>Haku...</i>
<i>Are you crying?</i>

191
00:15:43,947 --> 00:15:46,472
Thanks, Kakashi...

192
00:15:55,225 --> 00:15:57,693
You were always at my side...

193
00:15:59,162 --> 00:16:00,561
At the very least...

194
00:16:00,630 --> 00:16:03,599
I can be at your side in the end.

195
00:16:15,945 --> 00:16:17,970
If it's possible...

196
00:16:19,315 --> 00:16:22,443
I'd like to go...

197
00:16:24,721 --> 00:16:26,188
to the same place...

198
00:16:30,160 --> 00:16:31,218
as you.

199
00:16:52,515 --> 00:16:53,846
This guy...

200
00:16:53,917 --> 00:16:58,354
He was born in a village
where it snowed a lot.

201
00:17:00,557 --> 00:17:01,421
I see...

202
00:17:02,792 --> 00:17:05,522
He was a boy as pure as snow...

203
00:17:07,597 --> 00:17:09,565
You'd be able to go, Zabuza.

204
00:17:13,069 --> 00:17:15,094
The two of you... together.

205
00:17:18,908 --> 00:17:21,206
But you know, Kakashi Sensei...

206
00:17:21,678 --> 00:17:22,702
Hmm?

207
00:17:23,079 --> 00:17:24,979
I wonder if the way a Ninja
should be

208
00:17:25,381 --> 00:17:27,849
is really as these
two were saying.

209
00:17:30,053 --> 00:17:34,217
Shinobi should not seek
the reason for their own existence.

210
00:17:35,625 --> 00:17:38,788
What's important is to
exist merely as tools.

211
00:17:40,830 --> 00:17:42,821
That's the same in the Land of Leaves.

212
00:17:44,701 --> 00:17:46,692
I wonder if that's what
it really means

213
00:17:46,769 --> 00:17:48,896
to become a real Ninja.

214
00:17:49,672 --> 00:17:51,765
I guess... I guess!

215
00:17:51,841 --> 00:17:53,570
I don't like that!

216
00:17:54,777 --> 00:17:56,404
Do you think so, too?

217
00:17:56,813 --> 00:17:58,144
Hmm...

218
00:17:58,381 --> 00:18:02,147
Well... That's why all Ninja live

219
00:18:02,318 --> 00:18:06,584
trying to figure that
out without realizing...

220
00:18:07,824 --> 00:18:11,089
Like Zabuza... and that kid...

221
00:18:17,400 --> 00:18:18,298
Okay!

222
00:18:18,601 --> 00:18:19,397
Huh?

223
00:18:19,736 --> 00:18:21,363
I've just decided!

224
00:18:21,638 --> 00:18:24,664
I'm going to pursue my
own Way of Ninja!

225
00:18:25,241 --> 00:18:28,005
I'm gonna sprint straight
ahead and pursue

226
00:18:28,077 --> 00:18:31,342
a way that I absolutely
won't regret!

227
00:18:43,793 --> 00:18:47,388
Thanks to you the bridge
was safely completed,

228
00:18:47,630 --> 00:18:50,292
but we will miss you very much.

229
00:18:50,433 --> 00:18:51,764
Take care.

230
00:18:52,135 --> 00:18:53,534
Thank you for everything.

231
00:18:53,937 --> 00:18:55,234
Now, now!

232
00:18:55,305 --> 00:18:58,331
We'll come back for
a visit again, Tazuna!

233
00:19:00,076 --> 00:19:01,236
For sure?

234
00:19:01,411 --> 00:19:02,173
Huh?

235
00:19:06,716 --> 00:19:10,652
Inari... you're gonna
miss us, aren't you?

236
00:19:10,720 --> 00:19:13,416
It's all right to cry.
Go ahead and cry!

237
00:19:13,723 --> 00:19:14,951
I won't cry!

238
00:19:15,491 --> 00:19:18,460
It's all right if you cry,
Naruto!

239
00:19:18,795 --> 00:19:21,093
Oh, is that so?

240
00:19:27,937 --> 00:19:28,767
See ya!

241
00:19:28,838 --> 00:19:29,805
Oh...!

242
00:19:32,942 --> 00:19:34,807
<i>You are so stubborn.</i>

243
00:19:39,449 --> 00:19:42,543
That boy changed Inari's mind...

244
00:19:42,619 --> 00:19:45,713
and Inari changed the minds
of the village people.

245
00:19:46,623 --> 00:19:50,320
That boy created a bridge
linking us to hope,

246
00:19:50,393 --> 00:19:53,590
a bridge called courage.

247
00:19:54,731 --> 00:19:56,255
So a linking bridge...

248
00:19:57,033 --> 00:19:58,091
Speaking of bridges,

249
00:19:58,167 --> 00:20:00,101
we need to name
this bridge, don't we?

250
00:20:00,403 --> 00:20:01,631
That's true.

251
00:20:01,804 --> 00:20:02,930
In that case,

252
00:20:03,006 --> 00:20:06,635
I have a perfect name
for this bridge.

253
00:20:06,876 --> 00:20:08,639
Yeah, what is it?

254
00:20:09,112 --> 00:20:12,377
The Naruto Great Bridge!?
How's that?

255
00:20:13,983 --> 00:20:14,972
That's a good name.

256
00:20:15,852 --> 00:20:19,413
Okay! I'll get back soon
and have Iruka Sensei treat me

257
00:20:19,489 --> 00:20:22,185
to ramen as
the mission completion celebration!

258
00:20:22,659 --> 00:20:27,494
And! And! I'll tell Konohamaru
tales of my heroic exploits!

259
00:20:27,830 --> 00:20:29,457
Then I...

260
00:20:30,433 --> 00:20:32,526
Hey! Sasuke, do you want to go
on a date

261
00:20:32,602 --> 00:20:33,694
when we get back to the village?

262
00:20:34,070 --> 00:20:35,469
No, I don't think so.

263
00:20:35,605 --> 00:20:37,197
Just like that.?!

264
00:20:38,007 --> 00:20:40,976
You know! You know!
I'll go with you!

265
00:20:41,110 --> 00:20:42,077
Be quiet!

266
00:20:42,145 --> 00:20:43,134
Shut up! Naruto!

267
00:20:44,614 --> 00:20:47,845
What? Are you sure
that name's okay?

268
00:20:49,819 --> 00:20:54,916
This name is to wish that
this bridge will never collapse...

269
00:20:54,991 --> 00:20:59,587
And someday, it'll be the name
of a very famous bridge...

270
00:20:59,662 --> 00:21:02,688
A name heard around the world.

271
00:21:05,501 --> 00:21:08,368
That's truly what I hope.

272
00:22:52,909 --> 00:22:53,967
Hey, hey!

273
00:22:54,044 --> 00:22:56,774
Our Group Seven always
has the easy missions lately.

274
00:22:56,980 --> 00:22:59,005
Meanwhile, there are plenty of
powerful Ninja

275
00:22:59,082 --> 00:23:01,107
like Zabuza and Haku in other lands.

276
00:23:01,385 --> 00:23:05,378
Aren't there more exciting missions
where I can be more active?

277
00:23:05,756 --> 00:23:08,884
Where I can use my Way of
the Ninja and my soul like... you know?

278
00:23:10,193 --> 00:23:14,061
Next time:
"A New Chapter Begins:
The Chunin Exam!"

279
00:23:14,531 --> 00:23:16,328
This is my Way of Ninja!
